    <!-- Why AZERTY Global rather than AFNOR -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container container--narrow">
        <h2 class="section__title text-center">💡 Why AZERTY Global rather than AFNOR?</h2>

        <p class="mb-4 section-lead">
          AFNOR and AZERTY Global start from the same observation: the 1984 Windows AZERTY is outdated. But the two projects take radically different paths.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          AFNOR (NF Z71-300) proposes a <strong>complete overhaul</strong>: 40+ repositioned characters, new dead keys, accented capitals via <kbd>AltGr</kbd>+<kbd>Shift</kbd>. It's ambitious, but after 7 years (2019-2026), adoption remains near-nonexistent. The barrier to entry is too high.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4 text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          AZERTY Global makes the opposite choice: <strong>only 5 improvements</strong>, targeted at real everyday problems. Accented capitals are accessible with <kbd>Caps Lock</kbd> (a natural gesture), programming symbols are on the home row, and 99% of your habits stay intact.
        </p>

        <div class="card mb-4 border-l-accent-4">
          <p class="mb-2 text-secondary italic">
            “I tried the AFNOR standardized AZERTY for months. Then I tried AZERTY Global for 2 days. The winner: AZERTY Global, by far. Adjusting is super fast and it improves everything else.”
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold">— Gelth, IT professional</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Reorganizing everything to save a few theoretical milliseconds misses the point — the best layout is the one people actually adopt.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

